The Hooping Life is a 2010 documentary film directed by Amy Goldstein. The film had its world premiere in April 2010 at the Sarasota Film Festival, and focuses on the history of hooping.

== Synopsis ==
The film takes a look at the subculture of hula hooping, which was primarily spearheaded by women. Narrated by Shaquille ONeal, the documentary follows several people who participate in the subculture, incorporating it into their daily lives in various different ways.

